{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH7qsysqinrgsKeik17x","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. All tests pass.\n\n**Mechanism:** `paginate` sliced with `all.slice(start, start + size - 1)`. `Array.slice`'s second argument is the exclusive end index, so this returned only `size - 1` rows per page. The label in `summary.js` correctly computes `last = page*size`, so it advertised 10 rows while the pager delivered 9 — exactly the \"showing 1-10 of 23 but only 9 rows\" report. Changing the end index to `start + size` makes the slice return a full `size` rows.\n\nThe repro test (`test/paginate.test.js`) stays as the regression guard. The symptom appeared in the rendered label but the bug lived in `paginate.js`, not `summary.js` — `summary.js` was left untouched."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":260,"cache_read_input_tokens":24989,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":260},"output_tokens":6,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"011583f2-8692-4811-bfc2-4e78c76d8a1a","uuid":"00d13551-442a-478b-8723-93cf178c1284","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:45:52.350Z","request_id":"req_011CdH7qiW84ark2utnyDCyz"}
